UID:USAV_Florida_Region-2027_Florida_USAV_Gold_Series-2027-01-09T00:00:00
DESCRIPTION:EVENT BEGINS IN:\n\nEVENT SPONSOR:\nThe top 18 teams in the 13
 U-17U divisions in the Florida Region will be invited to compete at the Or
 ange County Convention Center. This event will award a National Bid to the
  winner of the 13U-17U divisions!\n\nREGISTRATION:\nThis is an invitation-
 only event. Teams will be accepted on a first come\, first served basis\, 
 after the following items have been completed:\n- Invitation Received - Te
 ams without an invitation will not be accepted\n- Completed Team Registrat
 ion\n- Payment Received - Payment by check will not be recorded until chec
 k is received by mail\n- Housing Verified - THIS EVENT IS A STAY-TO-PLAY E
 VENT (Housing will be available July 14\, 2026 at 12:00pm)\nOnce a divisio
 n has reached maximum capacity\, there is no guarantee a team will be acce
 pted into the event. Teams will be placed on a wait list and accepted on a
 n as-needed basis. The Florida Region will contact the team if a space bec
 omes available. Tournament staff reserves the right to modify the maximum 
 number of teams per division based on demand and bid impact.\n\nTEAM ENTRY
  FEES:\n2-Day Bid Divisions – $600*\n*The payment deadline is December 9
 th\, 2026 at 3PM. Payments made after that date will incur a late fee.\n\n
 INVITATION SCHEDULE:\n- Round 1 - July 13\, 2026 (top 18 teams in the 13U-
 17U divisions)\n- Round 2 - July 20\, 2026 (if necessary)\n- Round 3 - Jul
 y 27\, 2026 (if necessary)\nEligible teams will be sent an invitation to t
 he email address(es) listed in the club’s SportsEngine registration.\n\n
 REFUND POLICY:\nTeam Cancellation / Withdrawal Policy:\n- By December 9\, 
 2026 at 3:00pm - 100% Refund*\n- After December 9\, 2026 at 3:00pm - NO Re
 fund\n​*Refunds are less processing fees.\n\nADMISSION INFORMATION:\nAth
 lete and Coach entry will begin at 6:45am.\n- Coaches will need to present
  their assigned QR code and a corresponding photo ID at the entrance.\n- C
 haperones and parents cannot enter during the early access period.\nAccess
  for spectators will begin at 7:15am.\n\nHOUSING:\nThis is a stay-to-play 
 event. All housing requirements must be met no later than September 1\, 20
 26 at 3:00pm. After September 1\, 2026 at 3:00pm\, teams that are not comp
 liant will be dropped and wait list teams will be given notice of entry.\n
 The policy language below is being prepared in the form of frequently aske
 d questions with corresponding answers to help clarify the requirements fo
 r participating teams.\nIMPORTANT NOTE: Team Travel Source is the official
  event housing partner for the Florida Region.  All questions on event hot
 els for Florida Region should first be directed to Team Travel Source.  If
  additional information is needed beyond what Team Travel can provide\, pl
 ease contact the Florida Region office.\nPhone:  502-354-9103\nEmail: [em
 ail protected]\n\nFL REGION BID INFORMATION:\nThis tournament will award 
 the following bids to the GJNC:\n- 13U - 1 National​ Bid\n- 14U - 1 Nati
 onal Bid\n- 15U - 1 National Bid\n- 16U - 1 National Bid\n- 17U - 1 Nation
 al Bid\nNote: Open bids received after the event wi…\n\nMore info: https
 ://floridavolleyball.org/blog/event/2027-florida-usav-gold-series/
LOCATION:Orange County Convention Center\, West Hall - A1\, 9800 Internati
 onal Dr.\, Orlando\, FL 32819
URL:https://floridavolleyball.org/blog/event/2027-florida-usav-gold-series
 /
END:VEVENT
